"The key sequence <kbd>CTRL</kbd> + <kbd>C</kbd> is used to interrupt a "
"running command."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/books/admin_guide/03-commands.md:72
msgid "The use of a command generally follows this sequence:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/books/admin_guide/03-commands.md:76
msgid "```bash command [option(s)] [arguments(s)] ```"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/books/admin_guide/03-commands.md:78
msgid "The name of the command is **often in lower case**."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/books/admin_guide/03-commands.md:80
msgid "A space separates each item."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/books/admin_guide/03-commands.md:83
msgid ""
"Short **options** begin with a dash (`-l`), while **long options** begin "
"with two dashes (`--list`).  A double dash (`--`) indicates the end of the "
"option list."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/books/admin_guide/03-commands.md:85
msgid "It is possible to group some short options together:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/books/admin_guide/03-commands.md:89
msgid "```bash $ ls -l -i -a ```"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/books/admin_guide/03-commands.md:91
msgid "is equivalent to:"
