#. type: Plain text
#: docs/books/admin_guide/03-commands.md:225
msgid ""
"The `history` command displays the history of commands that have been "
"entered by the user.  The commands are stored in the `.bash_history` file in "
"the user's login directory."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/books/admin_guide/03-commands.md:227
msgid "Example of a history command"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/books/admin_guide/03-commands.md:233
msgid "```bash $ history 147 man ls 148 man history ```"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/books/admin_guide/03-commands.md:238
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"| Options | Comments                                                                                                           |\n"
"| ------- | ------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------ |\n"
"| `-w`    | The `-w` option will copy the history of the current session to it.                                                |\n"
"| `-c`    | The `-c` option will delete the history of the current session (but not the contents of the `.bash_history` file). |\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '* '
#: docs/books/admin_guide/03-commands.md:240
msgid "Manipulating history:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/books/admin_guide/03-commands.md:242
msgid ""
"To manipulate the history, the following commands entered from the command "
"prompt will:"
